President Barack Obama will be holding a news conference on Wednesday, July 22nd at the White House. The conference will be nationally televised at 9:00 PM EDT. Members of the media who wish to attend must apply for credentials by Monday, July 20th at 11:00 AM EDT. Even current White House hard pass holders must apply for credentials. The application process includes filling out a form and emailing personal information such as full name, date of birth, social security number, and country of citizenship. Riser positions have already been allocated, but a pool feed will be available. Applicants will be notified if their credentials have been granted by 6:00 PM EDT on Tuesday, July 21st.